# LEVEL 7: FORKING (Open Source Contribution)

---

## What is a Fork?

Fork is used to **copy a project from someone else's repository to your own repository**.

When you open someone's project and want to add it to yours to make some changes — just click **"Fork"** on GitHub.

Workflow:
```
Original Repository

↓

Fork

↓

Your GitHub Repository

↓

Clone

↓

Modify

↓

Push

↓

Pull Request
```

---

