# COMPLETE GIT WORKFLOW (End to End)

```
1. Create Repository on GitHub

↓

2. Clone Repository → git clone link

↓

3. Write Code

↓

4. git status

↓

5. git add .

↓

6. git commit -m "message"

↓

7. git push

↓

8. Repeat Steps 3–7

↓

9. Create Branch for New Feature → git checkout -b featurename

↓

10. Push Branch → git push origin featurename

↓

11. Create Pull Request on GitHub

↓

12. Senior reviews & Merges

↓

13. git pull origin main (to sync locally)
```


